Candice Bergen writes in her new memoir A Fine Romance that her father Edgar Bergen belittled her looks and favored his ventriloquist dummy Charlie McCarthy . 
  When he died in 1978 he left her out of his will - but Charlie was left $10,000 . 
  She was the highest paid actor in television for ten years playing the title role in Murphy Brown . 
  In her new book she reveals that she kept her salary secret from her mother . 
 